# reorG UI Conventions

## Visual Identity

- App: reorG by The Perfect Part
- Premium operational dashboard feel — not a generic admin template
- Dark mode default; light mode available via toggle
- Color scheme ties into The Perfect Part brand from www.theperfectpart.net
- High-contrast, clean, modern, professional

## Component Library

- Use shadcn/ui as the base component library
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling — no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Use Lucide icons (via lucide-react) — never use emojis as UI icons
- Use proper brand SVGs from Simple Icons for marketplace logos where applicable

## Layout

- Sidebar navigation on the left (collapsible)
- Top bar with app branding, user menu, theme toggle
- Main content area with proper padding
- Sticky search bar on the dashboard page
- No content hidden behind fixed elements

## Interaction Standards

- All clickable elements: `cursor-pointer`
- Hover feedback: color/opacity transitions (150-300ms) — no scale transforms that shift layout
- Focus states visible for keyboard navigation
- Modals close via X button and Esc key
- Links to marketplace listings open in new tabs (`target="_blank"` with `rel="noopener noreferrer"`)
- Confirm dialogs for all destructive or push operations

## Data Display

- Default timezone: America/New_York (configurable)
- Numbers: locale-formatted with appropriate decimal places
- Currency: USD with $ prefix, 2 decimal places
- Percentages: display with % suffix, 1-2 decimal places
- Dates: relative where recent ("2 min ago"), absolute where precision matters
- Use consistent number formatting across all pages

## Accessibility

- All images have alt text
- Form inputs have labels (visible or sr-only)
- Color is never the sole indicator — pair with icons, text, or patterns
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- Minimum contrast ratios: 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text

## Responsive

- Primary target: desktop (1280px+)
- Must remain functional at 1024px
- Mobile is not a priority but basic navigation should not break

## Design System Reference

- Global design rules: `design-system/MASTER.md`
- Page-specific overrides: `design-system/pages/{page-name}.md`
- When building a page, check for a page-specific override first; fall back to MASTER
